article.headline: Marist 28, Butler 10
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS -- Tommy Reilly threw for 283 yards and two touchdowns to lead Marist to a 28-10 victory against Butler on Saturday. Reilly completed 21 of 24 attempts for the Red Foxes (3-5, 2/3 Pioneer League). Tight end Anthony Calcagni had five receptions for 143 yards and a score. Andrew Huck threw for 78 yards on eight completions for the Bulldogs (4-4, 2-3) before leaving the game with an undisclosed injury after being sacked on the final play of the first half. Marist led 7-3 after the first quarter and broke the game open with a pair of second-quarter touchdowns: a 1-yard run by Matt Gray and 4-yard pass from Reilly to Byron Gardner. Jaquan Bryant had two interceptions for Marist.
